# Consulting Agentic Platform guardrails

## Think before coding
- Do not assume intent when the workflow, approval path, or state model is unclear.
- If behavior is ambiguous, say what is ambiguous before changing code.

## Simplicity first
- Write the minimum code needed.
- No speculative abstractions.
- No drive-by cleanup outside the requested scope.

## Surgical changes
- Every changed line should trace back to the task.
- Match local style and leave unrelated code alone.

## Explicit workflow architecture
- Do not hide agent policy in scattered string literals when a repo-visible surface can hold it.
- Do not call underscore-private orchestrator methods across module boundaries.
- Approval and production gate state should be durable and resumable.
- Keep one clear source of truth for workflow state.

## Verification
Before calling work done, verify the exact path you changed:
- gate approval/rejection
- resume behavior
- restart/durability path when relevant
- nearest backend/frontend tests
